 @Fayez alnaji  why would Donald need to know how to milk a cow. Also, please explain why you're suggesting one's ability to milk a cow equates to whether he can have an opinion, or not.

In the West, we buy milk in a store. We don't live our lives raising and tending to our food. We focus on whatever we are passionate about and eating and food is a very very small part of our life. Actually, we think about food about as much as any other bodily function. It's a necessity that doesn't define our worth, or value and certainly doesn't help us get a spouse.

I think the Dinka are amazing, but very different lifestyle than the averageWesterner. . I would love to live with you for a few months, or more.
